ent bonuses without necessarily benefiting the organization, such as holding on to depreciated assets, using absorption costing to build up inventory, and changing sales targets.\"", "\"QUIZ: ROI CALCULATION FOR DAMON CO\u2019S DIVISIONS\":\"This quiz involves calculating the ROI for one of Damon Co\u2019s divisions based on provided financial information, including revenue, variable costs, fixed operating costs, apportioned head office costs, interest charges, and tax.\"", "\"DIVISIONAL FIXED OPERATING COSTS\":\"Divisional fixed operating costs are expenses that do not change with the level of production or sales within a division, such as rent and salaries.\"", "\"APPORTIONED HEAD OFFICE COSTS\":\"Apportioned head office costs are the share of central administrative expenses allocated to a division.\"", "\"INTEREST CHARGES\":\"Interest charges are the costs incurred by a company for borrowed funds.\"", "\"TAX\":\"Tax is a compulsory financial charge imposed by a government on a company's income or profits.\"", "\"NET PROFIT\":Net profit is the amount of income left after all expenses, including taxes, interest, and head office costs, have been deducted from total revenue. In the year 20X0, net profit was calculated as $78,000 out of $200,000, resulting in a net profit margin of 39%. In the year 20X1, net profit was $80,000 out of $238,500, resulting in a net profit margin of 33.5%.", "\"EXPECTED ROI\":\"This quiz involves calculating the expected return on investment for a division based on given financial data, including non-current assets, working capital, and budgeted profit.\"", "\"BUDGET PROFIT OF ASSEMBLY CENTRE\":\"The quiz involves calculating the budget profit of the assembly centre, which receives all output from the machining profit centre. The budgeted sales volume is 120,000 units at a price of $26 per unit, with variable costs of $4 per unit and fixed costs of $350,000. The transfer price is set at variable cost plus 150%.\"", "\"BUDGETED PROFIT FOR 